cs.CR, cs.SY, cs.RO, cs.ET, cs.SE 

The paper discusses the vulnerabilities of control systems relying on inertial sensors and proposes attacks to manipulate the sensor output. This falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR) and system and control theory (cs.SY). The paper also discusses the use of inertial sensors in robotics (cs.RO) and embedded systems (cs.ET), and the attacks proposed could have implications for software engineering (cs.SE) in terms of designing secure control systems.
